&lt;h3&gt;Company Introduction&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Bot Auto, we build autonomous trucks to transform the way goods are transported and improve the quality of life for communities worldwide. With a start-up spirit yet long-established experience, Bot Auto has the most seasoned team that has delivered several world’s first and world’s only. Together, we share vision, we see and build miracles and we drive the future of transportation. Join us and turn your dream into something RUNNING.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Position Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Mechanical Engineer to join our Autonomous Hardware team. The successful candidate will play a key role in the design, development, and testing of mechanical systems and components for our autonomous vehicle platforms. This position requires a strong background in mechanical engineering, as well as a passion for innovation and problem-solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and optimize mechanical systems and components for autonomous vehicles, eg: sensor racks, equipment brackets, sensor cleaning system, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct simulations and analyses to validate design concepts and ensure performance and safety standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead rapid prototyping and function validation of the design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams including electrical engineers, software developers, and systems engineers to integrate mechanical systems into the overall vehicle architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and collaborate with local fabrication and manufacture suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the prototyping and testing of mechanical components, ensuring they meet specifications and performance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve mechanical issues, providing innovative solutions to enhance vehicle performance and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct failure analysis and implement corrective actions to improve design and manufacturing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in mechanical engineering and autonomous vehicle technology, applying new knowledge to ongoing projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain SOPs, train the technician for the truck retrofitting process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and revise BOMs to support the materials management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish the retrofitting process and quality control standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Required Skills:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering or a related field (Master’s degree preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in mechanical engineering, preferably in the automotive or autonomous vehicle industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in hands-on fabrication, 3D printing, power tools and hand tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CAD software (e.g., SolidWorks, CATIA, or equivalent) for designing mechanical components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of mechanical systems, materials, and manufacturing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CAE and other simulation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of automotive safety standards and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and the ability to present technical information clearly and concisely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
